      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-fb0986cc-7fff-7252-497f-732eaec66bc7\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Prerequisites </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">short leg</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">By spending 10 minutes whispering gentle encouragement to an ally, they are cured of one condition. This does not cure the cause of the condition, which may cause it to return (the next time one checks for an affliction, for example). If the cause was an ongoing spell, this allows the short leg to make a counteract attempt against it. On a failure, the condition is not removed.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>"
